An other good example is constructors; say you have a function like this:<p><pre><code>    function MyClass(x){
        this.x = x;
    }
</code></pre>
In Coffeescript this translates to<p><pre><code>    MyClass = (x) ->
        @x = x
</code></pre>
`x` is returned; and if you return something from a constructor, something is returned instead of the constructed object (`new MyClass({})` returns `{}`).
